Welcome to the release 1.2 of TACT.

This introductory message gives some information that will help
you get started using TACT.  To read more than what shows on the
screen, push the {B}PageDown{N} key.  To move "up" in this text, push
the {B}PageUp{N} key.


                       {B}What can I do now?{N}

Before you can make TACT do anything else, you must finish
looking at Help.  Do this by pushing either the "Enter" or "ESC"
key.

Following this, there are two ways to make TACT do something for
you:

    -  You can choose an action from the "Action Bar".  The
       Action Bar is shown on the top line of the screen.  To
       activate it, push either the "Enter" or "Space Bar" keys
       on your keyboard.  For more information on the Action Bar
       type the letter "{B}A{N}" now.

    -  You can push a function key.  In the bottom 4 lines on the
       screen you can see a summary of function key shortcuts.
       For more information on function key operations type "{B}S{N}"
       now.

If you have not yet read the TACT Guide, we urge you to look at
it now.  There is some general information about how TACT is
designed in two help items:
    -  {B}TACT's Working Lists{N}: go to it now by typing the letter
       "{B}L{N}".

    -  {B}TACT's Displays{N}: go to it now by typing the letter "{B}D{N}".


