Both TACT and MAKBAS are provided with a basic HELP facility.
HELP is meant to assist you while you are using TACT or MAKBAS by
reminding you of the formats of various commands, and the use of
the various function keys.  It is not intended that you learn
TACT from the HELP facility alone.  For this purpose, printed
documentation has been prepared, and you should read through it.

You access help by pushing either the F1 key or (from within
TACT) by choosing "HELP" from the action bar.  The help text that
you will see will vary depending upon what TACT is currently
doing for you.

TACT help works as follows:  TACT help is "context sensitive".
This means that the help screen it displays will change depending
on what TACT is doing at the time you push the F1 key.  Each help
message is called an "item".  After you've read the help message
you can dispose of it by pushing the ESC key, or pushing any
Function Key that indicates that you are ready to do some other
operation.

All Help text (including this introduction) is put into a window.
You use the UpArrow, DownArrow, Home, End, PgUp and PgDn keys to
see parts that currently don't fit in the window.

In addition, you can jump directly to a selected list of other
help items by typing certain letters.  To see what other help
items you can jump to, see the section at the end of the item
called "For More Help".


