컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴

You use the Rule Dialog Box when you want to ask TACT
automatically to select a list of words or text positions for
you.  Essentially, you must specify a set of criteria that will
tell TACT how to select for you.  TACT will then search its
databases, find the matching items, and create a "Search Result
List", from which you can further select items to create the
"Selected List".

Options are:

{B}Criteria{N}       Four lines are provided upon which you can specify
               the rule TACT is to use to select items for you.
               Criteria are specified in a language with a very
               specific syntax.  For help on the syntax, type "{B}S{N}"
               now.

{B}Config Context{N} You can specify a range of text to be used for
               collocation searches in this area of the screen.

{B}Manual Select{N}  If "Yes" is selected, TACT will present you with a
               selection window as soon as it has created its
               list of items.  If "No" is selected, TACT will not
               present you with a selection window.  You can, of
               course, always invoke the selection window
               yourself using the F3 key.

The Config Context options are:

{B}Unit{N}           Use this field to specify what structural unit
               should be used to define the context for various
               selection options.  To choose the unit from an

               available list, leave the field blank, or type a
               "?".

{B}Context Before{N} Number of units (given above) that should precede
               the unit containing the occurrence. *

{B}Context After{N}  Number of units (given above) that should follow
               the unit containing the occurrence. *


                              {B}Notes{N}

* To specify a context such as "sentence containing the
occurrence" (assuming that sentence is available as a structural
unit), specify Context Unit as "sentence", Before and After
values of "0".


