By pushing the F6 function key or choosing "Print" from the
Action Bar's "File" menu, you will cause TACT to print something
for you.  TACT can print three things for you:

    -  The active display.

    -  The contents of the current selection window

    -  A Help Item

Printing a Help item, or the current selection window is only
available by using the F6 function key, since the Action Bar
cannot be made active when inside a selection window, or a help
display.

The Print dialog box contains three fields:

    -  {B}Printer{N}: identifies which printer you want to print to.
       Valid options are "LPT1", "LPT2", "LPT3", "COM1" and
       "COM2".

    -  {B}Translation{N}: identifies which translation table TACT is to
       use when printing.  The translation table tells TACT how
       to print characters and certain attributes such as "bold".

    -  {B}Number of lines per page{N}: tells TACT how many lines you
       want per printer page (pages are separated by ASCII Form-
       Feed characters).  Put "0" (zero) if you want no page
       separation.

When you are ready to print, push the "Enter/Return" key.  To
avoid printing at this point, push the ESC key.  During printing
you can type any key to interrupt.


