Use this panel to control the characters MAKBAS will recognize as
letters, diacritics and the continuation character when
processing your text to produce a textual database.

To change the specification, move to the appropriate set of
fields and edit what's there.

Objects that this Panel controls are:

{B}Letters{N}        Characters that can appear in words and are used
               for alphabetization.

{B}Retained Diacritics{N}
               Symbols that are not letters for alphabetization
               purposes, but can appear within words, and should
               be retained as a part of the word.

{B}NonRetained Diacritics{N}
               Symbols, similar to Retained Diacritics, that may
               appear within a word, and are not to be considered
               for alphabetization purposes.  However, unlike
               Retained Diacritics, they will not be retained as
               a part of the word.

{B}Continuation Symbol{N}
               A symbol that, when appearing at the end of a line
               of text, indicates that the word continues on the
               next line.

When you are finished with this subpanel, push the "Enter/Return"
key.


