Use this panel to specify the text structure MAKBAS will
recognize while creating the textual database.  You can specify
the following information:

    o  Which of the pieces of structural information are to be
       given to TACT.

    o  How counters are organized hierarchically.

    o  How labels are to be recognized.

    o  Which BYU-type control data is to be recognized.

The information in this panel is maintained as a list.
Information about each character is stored as an entry in this
list.  You can perform the following types of operations on
entries:

   1.  {B}To create a new entry{N}, move to the end of the list (using
       the End key) and change the type switch from "Empty" to
       the type of entry you wish to create.

   2.  {B}To delete an existing entry{N}, find the entry you wish to
       dispose of (the PgUp and PgDn keys will move you between
       entries) and change the switch value to "Empty".

   3.  {B}To change an existing entry{N}, find the entry you wish to
       change and modify the fields to suit your purposes.  The
       Up and Down arrow keys will move you between fields in
       entries.


                   {B}Types of Objects Available{N}

    -  {B}Reference{N}: Choose this object to tell MAKBAS how to handle
       COCOA-like references in your text.

    -  {B}Label{N}: Choose this object to tell MAKBAS how to handle
       references which are differentiated by different types of
       brackets.

    -  {B}Counter{N}: Choose this object to tell MAKBAS how to handle
       references which are marked by single characters or short
       sequences in your text.  The counter value will be a
       number: the number of times the given character or
       characters occurred.

    -  {B}BYU{N}: Choose this object to tell MAKBAS how to handle
       references given in the BYU format.


                             {B}Fields{N}

{B}The "TACT ID:" field{N} is present in all submenus in the Structural
Information SubPanel.  On it you give the name or names by which
you wish to refer to the item when using TACT.  Although these
names are provided principally to give you access to the data in
TACT, they are also used within MAKBAS when you need to make a
reference from one type of structural information to another.

{B}The "Text ID:" field{N} is used in reference and BYU-type entries.
It is the place where you identify which Text reference you are
talking about.  For example, a COCOA-type reference "<a 1>" has a
Ref ID of "a".  The BYU reference "|a 1" has a Ref ID of "a"
also.

{B}Numeric:{N} This switch allows you to indicate whether the data
associated with the Ref ID are numeric.  Among other things,
tagging the data as numeric ensures that TACT will sort that data
numerically.

{B}Number of characters to keep:{N} If the value is a character string,
this option allows you to indicate how many characters from the
front of the string are to be passed to TACT.

{B}Open and Close Brackets:{N} These fields appear only in "label-type"
entries.  Use them to specify the type of brackets that surround
text labels.

{B}The counter ID{N} appears only in Counter entries and allows you to
specify what MAKBAS should look for in the text to increment the
counter.  There are two types of objects that can cause MAKBAS to
increment a counter:

   1.  One or more symbols.  In the case where the counter is
       associated with sentence punctuation, you would simply
       give the punctuation symbols, separated from each other by
       spaces, e.g.: {B}Counter ID: . ? !{N}

   2.  One or more text references or labels.  In this case, you
       first give an at-sign (``@''), and then immediately
       following one of the TACT names you have associated with
       the text reference or label that you wish to tie the
       counter to.

{B}Reset{N}: In this field (only in counters) you can enter the TACT
names of one or more other counters that are to be reset by the
occurrence of the present counter.  To reset a sentence counter
for each paragraph, enter the sentence counter name in the reset
field of the paragraph counter.

{B}Init{N}: In this field (in counter entries only) you can tell MAKBAS
what to set the counter to at the beginning, and what to reset it
to, when it is to be reset.

{B}Suppress Text{N}: This switch allows you to indicate whether or not
MAKBAS is to include the label as text in the textual database --
or not.  If "Yes", MAKBAS will process and extract the
information it finds and make it available to TACT, but the
actual display of the reference information as it appears in the
input text will not appear in the textual database saved for
TACT's use.


