Use the FREQ selection operator when you want to select words
based on frequency of occurrence.  When used as a source (e.g.
"{B}FREQ 5{N}"), FREQ selects words based on their frequency in the
entire text.  When used as a refinement (e.g. "{B}l.* ; FREQ 5{N}",
words are selected according to their number of occurrences in
the given list.

You give numbers to use as criteria for frequency selection.  The
forms are:

    o  You can give a single number, or number range: "{B}FREQ 5{N}" or
       "{B}FREQ 5:8{N}".

    o  You can use the "<", "<=", ">", or ">=" operators: "{B}FREQ{N}
       {B}<= 6{N}".

    o  If you enclose the specification in parentheses, you can
       specify more than one condition, separating each by a
       comma: "{B}FREQ (< 10, > 100){N}", "{B}FREQ (10:12, 50:58){N}".


