{B}Help: WHEN refinement{N}
컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴

The WHEN refinement allows you to select positions in the text
where a particular structural condition is true, for example,
when the speaker is Romeo.
The following is a partial description of WHEN refinement syntax.
For more information, refer to the TACT Guide.

An example of WHEN refinement in use is:

     lov.* ; when speaker = romeo


                  {B}Simple WHEN Selection Format{N}

The general format of the basic WHEN selection is:

     {B}<choose from> ; WHEN <Ref ID> = <selection list>{N}

The elements are:

{B}<choose from>{N}  This is the specification for the primary list
               from which the WHEN specification will choose in
               order to create a secondary list.  The <choose
               from> specification is often a word, word list, or
               regular expression, but it can be created in other
               ways.

{B}<Ref ID>{N}       This is the name of the piece of structural
               information we want to use as the basis of our
               refinement selection.  To select from a list of
               possible items for this database, enter a "?" in
               the specification.

{B}<selection list>{N}
               This element tells TACT to include in the
               resulting list a particular occurrence from the
               <choose from> list when the occurrence is found in
               a context that has the given value(s) for <Ref
               ID>.  To select from a list of possible items for
               this database, enter a "?" in the specification.
               This will only work if the unit is not numeric.

The selection list format can be:

    o  A single name: ... ; WHEN speaker = {B}juliet{N}

    o  A list of names (separated by commas): ... ; WHEN speaker
       = {B}romeo, juliet{N}

    o  A range of numbers (if reference is numeric): ... ; WHEN
       chapter = {B}10:15{N}

    o  If reference is numeric, you can use "<", ">", "<=" and
       ">=": ... ; WHEN chapter {B}< 15{N}

    o  A question mark (to choose from list -- if reference is
       {B}not{N} numeric): ... ; WHEN speaker = {B}?{N}

    o  A regular expression: ... ; WHEN speaker = {B}j.*{N}


