{B}Help: TACT's Collocate Display{N}
컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴

The Collocate display produces a list of collocates for each word
or word-pattern sorted into descending order by their z-scores (a
measure of the attraction of the collocate to the word or word-
pattern, based on a comparison of the expected number of co-
occurrences (assuming a random distribution through the text) to
the actual number of co-occurrences within the span.

    -  {B}To move about in the display{N}: use the Home, End, PgUp,
       PgDn, Up, Down, or Left and Right cursor keys.  Moving the
       selected node in the display will change the current
       position in the text.

    -  {B}To Change the type of display{N}: choose "Current" or "New"
       from the Action Bar.  Other display types are KWIC, Index
       and Text.

    -  {B}To Change some option associated with the Collocate{N}
       {B}Display{N}: push the F4 Key.

The top line of the display contains the following information:

    -  The reference information for the current position.

    -  The number of words in the "mini-text": the text near to
       the positions in the selected list from which the
       collocates have been drawn.

    -  The total number of words in the entire database.

Following this are several columns of information.  The next two
lines on the display are labels for the columns.  The display has
two modes of operation, showing or suppressing intermediate
results that are produced to calculate the Z-score.  In short
form (suppressing intermediate results) the following data is
displayed:

    -  {B}Collocates:{N}  In this column are the collate word types
       that TACT found.

    -  {B}Sel. Node:{N}  This column is used to indicate the current
       position in the selected list.  By pushing the Up and Down
       arrow keys, or the PgUp and PgDn keys you can change the
       current position (in the same way as you can for other
       displays).  Pushing the Left and Right arrow keys will
       move you between different occurrences of the current
       collocate headword (if more than 1 occurrence is
       represented in the display).

    -  {B}Collocate Freq:{N}  This is the number of times the collocate
       occurred in the mini-text.

    -  {B}Type Freq:{N}  This is the number of times the word occurred
       in the entire text.

    -  {B}Z-score:{N}  This is the Z-score for the collocate.

The remaining information only appears when intermediate results
are being displayed:

    -  {B}Type Prob.:{N} This is the probability calculated by taking
       the total number of occurrences of the word throughout the
       text and dividing it by the text size.
    -  {B}Expected Observ.:{N} This is the number of observations of
       the word you'd expect to find in the mini-text, based on
       its probability (calculated above).

    -  {B}Standard Dev.:{N} This is the standard deviation, calculated
       for use within the Z-score.


