Welcome to COLLGEN for TACT system 1.2.

The rest of this introduction message is a some information that
will help to get you started using COLLGEN.  To read more than
what shows on the screen, push the {B}PageDown{N} key.  To move "up" in
this text, push the {B}PageUp{N} key.


                        {B}What is COLLGEN?{N}

COLLGEN is a part of the TACT system that can take a TDB file and
produce a complete list of all phrases (where "phrase" simply
means repeated word groups of 2 or more words) found in the TDB
text.  The phrases COLLGEN found can be printed, written to a
file, or stored as a "RUL" file for subsequent use within TACT.


                       {B}What can I do now?{N}

Before you can make COLLGEN do anything else, you must finish
looking at Help.  Do this by pushing either the "Enter" or "ESC"
key.

After you've finished looking at this Help message you can do
three things:

   1.  You can stop COLLGEN immediately by pushing the F10 key.

   2.  You can check over and alter if necessary the assumptions
       COLLGEN will make about the text file it is about to work
       on.

   3.  When you're ready you can ask COLLGEN to proceed to create
       the collocation lists by pushing the "Enter/Return" or
       "F9" function keys.


                       {B}On the Front Panel{N}

The fields on the front panel provide COLLGEN with the following
information:

    o  {B}Input Database{N}: Give the name of the TDB database you want
       to process here.

    o  {B}Temporary FIle Area{N}: Optionally, specify a device and/or
       path where you wish COLLGEN to put its temporary working
       files.  Unless you have a special place to put temporary
       files (such as a large RAM disk, for example) leave this
       field blank.

    o  {B}Span Context{N}: Specify the number of words you want to
       consider for a phrase.  The default, "2 to 2 words",
       indicates that all 2 word phrases are to be considered.
       "2 to 3 words" would indicate all 2 or 3 word phrases.

    o  {B}Number of repetitions to keep{N}: Specify how many times the
       word phrase has to occur to be considered by COLLGEN.  The
       default, "2 or more" indicates that a phrase will appear
       in the output if it occurs 2 or more times in the text.


    o  {B}Generate Collocations{N}: Choose one of the options: "To
       Disk" means that the results will be put in a file.  "To
       Printer" means that the results will be sent to your
       printer.  "No" means that no printed output is desired.

    o  {B}Output File Name{N}: If "To Disk" is chosen, you can specify
       the name of a file to use for the output.  COLLGEN will
       create a default name by taking the name of the TDB file
       and replacing the given filename extension with ".COL".

    o  {B}Generate Rule File{N}: Choose "Yes" to ask COLLGEN to
       generate a RULE file for use within TACT.

    o  {B}Rule File Name{N}: If a Rule File is requested, you can
       specify the name of the rule file here.  COLLGEN will
       create a default name by taking the name of the TDB file
       and replacing the given filename extension with ".RUL".
