{B}Help: TACT's Scripts: Creating a Comment Window{N}
컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴

Type in the text you wish TACT to display during script playback
into this comment window.  Although TACT does not provide you
with a full word-processor in which to enter your text it gives
you a few very basic facilities.  In addition to the field-
editing features described elsewhere, the following keys are
supported:

    o  {B}Down Arrow{N}: will move you to the next line

    o  {B}Up Arrow{N}: will move you to the previous line

    o  {B}F5{N}: will allow you to resize the comment window

    o  {B}Ctrl-F5{N}: will allow you to place the comment window on the
       screen

    o  {B}Home{N}: will move you to the first line

    o  {B}End{N}: will move you to the last line

    o  {B}Esc{N}: will make TACT remove the comment window without
       creating it.

    o  {B}Enter/Return{N}: will make TACT create the comment window you
       have entered and put it in the script file.


